## The Situation So Far

Annie's roommate has been trying positive reinforcement techniques to get Johnny (the 6-year-old she babysits) to go to bed, but they aren't working out like she thought.

**What's happening:**
- She rewards him for going to his room by letting him play with his favorite toys before bed
- After a while, she tells him to put away his toys in a box in his room, which he does
- But when she tells him to get into bed, he runs away from the room laughing whenever "bed" is mentioned
- She chases after him and keeps nagging him to go to bed
- He eventually gets tired and goes to bed, but she's left feeling tired and frustrated
    </Markdown>

