  <!-- Lin's notes on 4 functions -->
  <Markdown id="four_functions_notes">
## The Four Functions of Behavior

Lin's notes from class:

The four main functions of behavior are:

| Function | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| **Attention** | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Behavior occurs to get attention from others |
| **Escape** | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Behavior occurs to avoid or get away from something |
| **Access** | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Behavior occurs to gain access to a preferred activity or object |
| **Sensory** | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Behavior occurs because it feels good (automatic reinforcement) |

    </Markdown>

