  <Markdown id="abc_example">
## ABC Example: Escape

Let's look at an example:

| Component | Example |
|-----------|---------|
| **Antecedent** | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Teacher gives a difficult task |
| **Behavior** | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Student puts head down |
| **Consequence** | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Task is removed or delayed |
| **Function** | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;**Escape** |

**JJ explains:** The teacher gave a hard task, then the student put their head down instead of working on it. Then the teacher probably got sick of waiting and gave up on making them do it, or just assigned it for homework.

**Lin adds:** Right, the student continued to put their head down for so long that maybe the teacher just delayed the task. Either way, the student successfully escaped the aversive task.
    </Markdown>

