  <!-- Implementation fidelity introduction -->
  <Markdown id="fidelity_intro">
## Implementation Fidelity

The team showed the progress to the professor, explaining that the roommate admitted she didn't follow all of the consequence strategies.

**Professor:** "Looks like you need to improve on **implementation fidelity**."

**Implementation fidelity** refers to how accurately and consistently a behavior plan is implemented as it was designed.

### Key Aspects of Fidelity:

| Aspect | Question |
|--------|----------|
| **Adherence** | Are all steps of the plan followed as written? |
| **Dosage** | Is the plan used for the correct amount of time/frequency? |
| **Quality of Delivery** | Are strategies implemented correctly with intended tone/approach? |
| **Participant Responsiveness** | Is the child actually exposed to and engaged with the intervention? |
| **Program Differentiation** | Are other strategies (not part of the plan) avoided during implementation? |
    </Markdown>

